---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Research">
	<section class="mb-16 pt-4">
		<h1 class="mb-12 text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-black md:text-6xl">Research</h1>

		<div class="space-y-20">
			<div class="group">
				<h2
					class="group-hover:text-reaim-blue mb-6 text-3xl font-bold text-black transition-colors"
				>
					Reliable AI for High-Dimensional Multimodal Health Data
				</h2>

				<p class="mb-8 max-w-4xl text-xl leading-relaxed text-gray-800">
					We are developing AI models for clinical and biomedical data for meaningful downstream
					tasks. Brute forcing existing inductive biases and architectures can lead to unreliable
					scientific inference and predictions. Therefore, the lab focuses on developing data
					representations, learning tasks, and model architectures that will be
					<span class="font-bold text-black">robust to large distributional shifts</span>, and
					evaluated with robust frameworks to test inferential capabilities.
				</p>

				<div
					class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 bg-gray-50 p-6 transition-shadow hover:shadow-md md:p-8"
				>
					<div class="flex flex-col items-start gap-6 md:flex-row">
						<div>
							<h3 class="mb-2 text-xl leading-tight font-bold md:text-2xl">
								<a
									href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2505.16953"
									target="_blank"
									class="hover:text-reaim-blue text-black transition-colors hover:underline"
								>
									ICYM2I: The illusion of multimodal informativeness under missingness
								</a>
							</h3>
							<p class="mb-2 text-lg text-gray-600">
								<span class="text-reaim-blue font-bold">Young Sang Choi*, Vincent Jeanselme*,</span> Pierre
								Elias, <span class="text-reaim-blue font-bold">Shalmali Joshi</span>
							</p>
							<p class="text-gray-500 italic">
								International Conference on Learning Representations (ICLR) 2026
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="group">
				<h2
					class="group-hover:text-reaim-blue mb-6 text-3xl font-bold text-black transition-colors"
				>
					Adaptive AI Systems for Generalizability
				</h2>

				<p class="mb-8 max-w-4xl text-xl leading-relaxed text-gray-800">
					Enabling systems that generalize to out-of-distribution data requires adaptive AI
					approaches where models can improve from their mistakes. We leverage <span
						class="font-bold text-black"
						>probabilistic modeling, reinforcement learning, and deep learning</span
					> to overcome imperfections of observational health and medicine data and develop adaptive multimodal
					AI systems.
				</p>

				<div
					class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 bg-gray-50 p-6 transition-shadow hover:shadow-md md:p-8"
				>
					<div class="flex flex-col items-start gap-6 md:flex-row">
						<div>
							<h3 class="mb-2 text-xl leading-tight font-bold md:text-2xl">
								<a
									href="https://openreview.net/pdf?id=uuQQwrjMzb"
									target="_blank"
									class="hover:text-reaim-blue text-black transition-colors hover:underline"
								>
									Adaptive Labeling for Efficient Out-of-distribution Model Evaluation
								</a>
							</h3>
							<p class="mb-2 text-lg text-gray-600">
								Daksh Mittal, Yuanzhe Ma, <span class="text-reaim-blue font-bold"
									>Shalmali Joshi</span
								>, and Hongseok Namkoong
							</p>
							<p class="text-gray-500 italic">
								Neural Information Processing Systems (NeurIPS) 2024
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="group">
				<h2
					class="group-hover:text-reaim-blue mb-6 text-3xl font-bold text-black transition-colors"
				>
					Foundation Models in Health and Medicine
				</h2>

				<p class="mb-8 max-w-4xl text-xl leading-relaxed text-gray-800">
					We develop and benchmark AI models in-house and in collaboration with clinical experts.
					Our goal is to highlight current limits and provide improvements so we can use AI models
					as <span class="font-bold text-black">expert reasoning agents</span>. Our current
					applications are in psychiatry, cardiology, radiology, rheumatology, and neurocritical
					care.
				</p>

				<div
					class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 bg-gray-50 p-6 transition-shadow hover:shadow-md md:p-8"
				>
					<div class="flex flex-col items-start gap-6 md:flex-row">
						<div>
							<h3 class="mb-2 text-xl leading-tight font-bold md:text-2xl">
								<a
									href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2505.16941"
									target="_blank"
									class="hover:text-reaim-blue text-black transition-colors hover:underline"
								>
									FoMoH: A clinically meaningful foundation model evaluation for structured
									electronic health records
								</a>
							</h3>
							<p class="mb-2 text-lg text-gray-600">
								Chao Pang, <span class="text-reaim-blue font-bold"
									>Vincent Jeanselme, Young Sang Choi,</span
								> Xinzhuo Jiang, <span class="text-reaim-blue font-bold"
									>Zilin Jing, Aparajita Kashyap, Yuta Kobayashi,</span
								> Yanwei Li, <span class="text-reaim-blue font-bold">Florent Pollet,</span> Karthik Natarajan,
								<span class="text-reaim-blue font-bold">Shalmali Joshi</span>
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
